Linus and Luke react to new humanoid robot demos from Engine AI and Unitree. They break down why the T800 video looks fake, from lighting to the lack of human interaction, while the H2 seems more believable thanks to real people interacting with it. They debate which robots might actually perform as advertised and call out the staged, over-polished nature of these viral clips.
